 Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API \u2014 see /api/consensus)*\\n| 1 | culture | Paper trading mode is required before any live order submission. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit founder approval. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | culture | mean_reversion is our primary strategy (85.7% win rate in backtests). momentum and crypto_edge are disabled \u2014 10-11% win rates. Do not re-enable without data. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 3 | culture | All API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Pattern: check Bearer token before processing. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 4 | culture | Confidence threshold is 0.80 minimum for signal execution. Signals below 80% confidence are filtered by SignalEngine. Do not lower this threshold without backtesting. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 5 | decision | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All trading infrastructure targets the Kalshi prediction market API. Task 236 blocks live API until credentials obtained from kalshi.com. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 6 | group | When you learn something important about strategy, security, or architecture \u2014 post a culture entry via: curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"culture\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"section\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\"}\\\" | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 7 | culture | Sprint 2 test coverage is complete: unit tests for PnL (T286), screener (T287), win probability (T288), mean reversion (T279), and CI runner (T289) all done. Run `npm test` for full suite. 96 unit + 30 integration + 576 E2E tests. Two pre-existing integration failures in smoke_test and mia_integration are known backend issues, not runner bugs. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 8 | decision | Sprint 2 complete (2026-04-03). Trading system now has full test coverage + CI. Cloud deployment plan ready (ECS Fargate ~$29/mo). Mobile push notification spec done. Remaining blocker before live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). Next sprint should focus on: cloud deploy execution, paper trade P&L validation, and live trading readiness. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 9 | decision | Sprint 3 complete. CRITICAL: mean_reversion live win rate is 18.2% vs 85.7% backtest (67pp gap). Paper PnL: -$13.73 over 19 trades. 4 trades had NULL signal_confidence. DO NOT go live until divergence is resolved. Sprint 4 is focused on root cause analysis (Grace T322), parameter tuning (Ivan T324), and paper trading automation (Bob T323). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 10 | decision | CORRECTION (T322, Grace): The 85.7% backtest win rate was incorrect \u2014 actual backtest win rate is 55.9% (209/374 trades). Live win rate is 18.2%, gap is 37pp not 67pp. ROOT CAUSE: live_runner.js fetchCandles() uses Math.random() for mock candle data, producing meaningless signals. Fix required: replace random mock with deterministic synthetic or real historical data before paper trade metrics are meaningful. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 11 | decision | Sprint 4 complete (2026-04-03). fetchCandles() bug fixed (T326): replaced Math.random() with ticker-seeded deterministic PRNG. Paper trade metrics are now reproducible and meaningful. Next step: run paper trades with fixed data and compare win rate against 55.9% backtest baseline. Ivan param tuning recommendations (T324) should be applied once initial paper trade results confirm baseline recovery. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 12 | decision | Sprint 5 complete (2026-04-03). NULL signal_confidence bugs fixed (T331): live_runner.js now passes confidence field in trade output, pnl_tracker.js reads trade.confidence instead of hardcoding null, SignalEngine has null guard. Paper trade validation (T327) delivered 51 trades + /api/pnl/live endpoint. Trade settlement auto-running (T330). Current win rate: 35% live vs 55.9% backtest (21pp gap). Remaining blocker for live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials \u2014 Founder action required). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 13 | culture | Divergence analysis tool delivered (agents/bob/backend/scripts/divergence_analyzer.js). Current live paper win rate: 35.0% (60 trades) vs backtest 55.9% (374 trades). Gap is statistically significant (p=0.001). Live avg trade PnL: -22.18\u00a2 vs backtest +24.76\u00a2. Backtest worst market: INXW-25-DEC31 (23.3% WR). Live markets differ from backtest markets \u2014 market selection bias may be a factor. Recommendation: do not go live until gap <10pp; apply param tuning (lookback 20, z=2.0) and collect 100+ paper trades. Run: node backend/scripts/divergence_analyzer.js | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 14 | culture | Live paper trade win rate (30.4% over 69 trades) diverges significantly from mean_reversion backtest (55.9%, 374 trades). Z-score = -4.17 (p < 0.05). All 3 paper-traded markets are underwater. Do NOT go live until gap is within 5pp or root cause is identified. Real Kalshi API data (T236) and larger sample size (200+ trades) required before go/no-go decision. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 15 | culture | Parameter sweep analysis (agents/bob/backend/scripts/parameter_sweep.js) reveals that deterministic mock data in fetchCandles() is too simplistic for meaningful parameter tuning. All zScore thresholds 0.8-3.0 produce identical signals on the same 8 fallback markets because mock candles have artificially low variance, creating extreme z-scores every time. Lookback changes do not materially affect signal quality. Conclusion: the deterministic PRNG fix made data reproducible, but the synthetic data model itself is not realistic enough to validate strategy parameters. We need either (a) real historical Kalshi data, or (b) a more sophisticated synthetic generator with regime shifts and realistic volatility, before paper trade metrics can be trusted for live go/no-go decisions. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 16 | culture | Built synthetic market generator (agents/bob/backend/scripts/synthetic_market_generator.js) to replace simplistic deterministic fallback. Comparison shows legacy mock data always produced mean~85 with stddev~2.5, creating extreme z-scores (-7 to +11) and guaranteed 0.95 confidence signals. New generator uses Ornstein-Uhlenbeck with market-appropriate volatility: crypto stddev~6-8, econ stddev~2-4, creating realistic z-scores. However, SignalEngine minConfidence=0.80 combined with MeanReversionStrategy confidence=-z-/3 means only markets with -z->=2.4 generate signals. On realistic synthetic data, most markets fall below this threshold. This may explain low live signal counts. Consider lowering minConfidence to 0.65 or changing confidence formula to -z-/2.0 for better signal generation. Run: node backend/scripts/test_synthetic_vs_legacy.js | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 17 | culture | CRITICAL FIX applied to live_runner.js fetchCandles() mock fallback (Tina). Root cause of live/backtest divergence identified: mock candles were centered on hardcoded basePrice (16/56/86) instead of current market price. This created extreme z-scores (e.g., current=64 vs mean=89.7, z=-11.2) and guaranteed 95% confidence signals on every run. FIX: fetchCandles() now accepts currentPriceHint (market.yes_mid) and centers synthetic history around actual market price. Result: means now align with current prices (e.g., current=64, mean=66.8), producing realistic z-scores. With aligned zScoreThreshold=1.5, mock fallback now correctly generates 0 signals because these markets are not actually mispriced. This confirms the previous live paper trades were artifacts of bad mock data, not real edge. Trade-off: paper trading in mock mode will produce few/no signals until API credentials provide real market history. Run: node backend/strategies/live_runner.js --execute | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 18 | decision | Sprint 6 complete (2026-04-03). Key outcome: ALL prior paper trade win rates (18.2%, 35%, 30%) were artifacts of broken mock data (fetchCandles() used hardcoded base prices \u2192 extreme z-scores \u2192 guaranteed signals). Fix applied (Tina, T326): candles now centered on market.yes_mid. Correct behavior: 0 signals on mock data. Momentum/crypto_edge hard-disabled (T325). Dashboard win rate trend chart added (T327). Realistic OU synthetic generator built (T328). System is ready \u2014 only T236 (Kalshi API credentials) blocks meaningful paper/live trading. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 19 | decision | Parameter sweep (T334, Ivan) complete \u2014 96 combinations tested on 50 markets. Recommended (Balanced): zScoreThreshold=1.2, lookback=10, confidenceThreshold=0.65 (94.4% win rate, 18 signals). Max Win Rate alt: zScoreThreshold=0.8, lookback=10, confidenceThreshold=0.75 (100% WR, 10 signals). NOTE: results based on synthetic replay data \u2014 validate against real Kalshi data (T236) before treating as authoritative. Previous default confidenceThreshold=0.80 was too strict; 0.65 recommended. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 20 | decision | Sprint 7 complete (2026-04-03). Delivered: replay backtest engine (T332/bob), dashboard status page with Kalshi credential banner + backtest results (T333/charlie), optimized params zScore=1.2 lookback=10 confidence=0.65 from 96-combo sweep (T334/ivan), live trading prep script + go/no-go checklist requiring >40% win rate on 10 real paper trades (T335/grace). System fully ready for T236 (Kalshi API credentials) to unlock live trading. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 21 | culture | Applied T334 optimized parameters across all pipeline scripts (Tina). Changes: live_runner.js CANDLE_DAYS=10 (was 30), SignalEngine minConfidence=0.65 (was 0.80), MeanReversionStrategy zScoreThreshold=1.2 (was 1.5). Same params applied to kalshi_api_validator.js and run_synthetic_paper_trade.js for consistency. E2E smoke test passes (7/7). With corrected mock data centering + optimized params, live_runner now generates 1 realistic signal per run in mock mode instead of 0 or 3+ artifacts. Ready for real Kalshi data validation (T236). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 22 | culture | UI audit test entry - can be ignored | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 23 | decision | D004 STRATEGIC DIRECTION: Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou). 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering by volume + yes/no ratio (15-30%, 70-85% targets), (2) LLM embedding-based clustering for related markets, (3) Pearson correlation detection for price pairs, (4) C++ high-frequency execution (<1ms latency). Phases 1-3 run daily, Phase 4 trades in real-time. This is the real edge \u2014 every agent decision should orient toward this. Reference: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab Pearson approach. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n| 24 | decision | STRATEGIC COMMITMENT: D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star. Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). Sprint 8 phases 1-3 complete with deliverables flowing (markets_filtered.json \u2192 market_clusters.json \u2192 correlation_pairs.json). Sprint 9 begins Phase 4 C++ implementation with Dave + Alice integration. ALL unrelated work is deprioritized until D004 Phase 4 is live and validated. This is the real edge that makes Agent Planet profitable. | lord | 2026-04-03 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":1,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"from_alice_t353_unblocked.md\",\"preview\":\"# T353 UNBLOCKED \u2014 Start Paper Trade Validation Now\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"353\",\"title\":\"SPRINT 11: Paper Trade Validation (Pre-Live Testing)\",\"description\":\"Run full engine in paper trading mode. Execute 200+ trades across 6 arbitrage pairs. Metrics: win rate (target >40%), avg PnL, Sharpe ratio, max drawdown (<10%), circuit breaker validation. Output: paper_trade_report.md (win rate by pair), metrics_dashboard.json, risk_analysis.md. Success: Win rate \u226540%, no false positives.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Sprint 11: paper trading validation\"},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"353\",\"title\":\"SPRINT 11: Paper Trade Validation (Pre-Live Testing)\",\"description\":\"Run complete Kalshi arbitrage engine in paper trading mode against real market data. Execute 200+ paper trades across 6 arbitrage pairs (from T345). Collect metrics: win rate (target: >40%), avg trade PnL, Sharpe ratio, max drawdown (<10%), circuit breaker triggers. Validate risk controls work in practice. Output: paper_trade_report.md (win rate breakdown by pair/market condition), metrics_dashboard.json, risk_analysis.md (drawdown study, tail risk). Success: Win rate \u226540%, no circuit breaker false positives, ready for go/no-go decision.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Sprint 11 paper trade validation. Input: Phase 4 engine from T351 + E2E tests from T352.\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_28_14_alice_critical_finding.md\",\"preview\":\"# CRITICAL: Prior Paper Trade Metrics Were Artifacts \u2014 Strategy Status Reset **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Root Cause Found (Tina, Culture #17) All win rates we've been tr\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_25_19_alice_sprint6_update.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 6 Update \u2014 Root Cause Clarifying **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Tina's Analysis + Culture #15 \u2014 Key Finding The win rate gap is statistically significant (Z=-4.17,\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_21_tina_divergence_analysis.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update: Live vs Backtest Divergence Analysis **From:** Tina (General Engineer)   **Date:** 2026-04-03 I ran a statistical analysis of our live paper trades vs the mean_reversion backtest baseli\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_t352_complete_t353_ready.md\",\"preview\":\"# T352 COMPLETE \u2014 Phase 4 E2E Integration Done \u2705 T353 Ready to Start \ud83d\ude80 **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-03  \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_t352_complete_critical_path_unblocked.md\",\"preview\":\"# T352 COMPLETE \u2705 \u2014 Critical Path Unblocked, Sprint 10 Done **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-03  \"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0017_RESUME_2026_04_06_13_05_37_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) \u2014 do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions \u2014 managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending \u2192 claimed (in_progress) \u2192 done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL \u2014 Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH \u2014 Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code \u2014 execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files \u2014 the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter \u2192 cluster \u2192 correlate \u2192 generate signals \u2192 simulate trades \u2192 produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated \u2014 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2\u21923 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets \u2192 Grace filters \u2192 Ivan clusters \u2192 Bob correlates \u2192 Dave simulates \u2192 Tina QA \u2192 Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":4,\"urgent\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_12_14_48_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"# Sprint 4 \u2014 From Founder\\n\\nGrace \u2014 you have T579 (Phase 1 filter).\\nWait for a DM from Bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready.\\nThen: read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json, apply Phase 1 filter, output to output/filtered_markets.json\\nDM ivan when done.\\n\"}],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_12_27_41_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# T578 Kalshi API Client Ready \u2014 Handoff to Grace\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_02_34_11_from_dave.md\",\"preview\":\"T568 rework done \u2014 spread-based P&L now. 22 trades from 47 signals, 22.7% win, -$1.33 P&L. Strategy \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_00_48_22_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# T569 APPROVED\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"579\",\"title\":\"Phase 1: Filter mock markets by volume and YES/NO ratio\",\"description\":\"Grace: Wait for DM from bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready. Run Phase 1 filter (volume \u226510000, YES/NO 15-30% or 70-85%). Read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Output filtered results to output/filtered_markets.json. DM ivan: \\\"filtered_markets.json ready \u2014 N markets passed, run Phase 2 clustering\\\". Post milestone to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"data\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-06\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-06\",\"notes\":\"Depends on T578. Handoff: grace \u2192 ivan\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_12_10_00_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Codex Running From: Alice Date: 2026-04-06 codex is running\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_20_20_00_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# T587 Complete: Capital Floor Safety Check **From:** Bob (Backend Engineer) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Built `capital_floor.js` \u2014 prevents negative capital in backtesting and live trading: - **$50 capital \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_20_15_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Quality Gate: 6/7 Reviewed \u2014 All PASS **From:** Olivia (TPM 2 \u2014 Quality) **Date:** 2026-04-04 Sprint 4 quality gate (T584) nearly complete: | Task | Agent | Verdict | QA Tests |\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_sprint4_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff \u2014 Kalshi API Readiness & Pipeline Hardening **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-04\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_00_39_21_sprint3_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 3 Kickoff \u2014 Production Quality via Collaboration **Theme:** Every task has explicit handoffs. Use DMs, team_channel, and peer reviews. ## New Culture Norms\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0002_RESUME_2026_04_07_00_36_50_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) \u2014 do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions \u2014 managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending \u2192 claimed (in_progress) \u2192 done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL \u2014 Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH \u2014 Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code \u2014 execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files \u2014 the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter \u2192 cluster \u2192 correlate \u2192 generate signals \u2192 simulate trades \u2192 produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated \u2014 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2\u21923 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets \u2192 Grace filters \u2192 Ivan clusters \u2192 Bob correlates \u2192 Dave simulates \u2192 Tina QA \u2192 Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| 3 | culture | pipes-should-become-dashes | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 4 | group | type pipe sanitization regression guard | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":0,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"579\",\"title\":\"Phase 1: Filter mock markets by volume and YES/NO ratio\",\"description\":\"Grace: Wait for DM from bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready. Run Phase 1 filter (volume \u226510000, YES/NO 15-30% or 70-85%). Read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Output filtered results to output/filtered_markets.json. DM ivan: \\\"filtered_markets.json ready \u2014 N markets passed, run Phase 2 clustering\\\". Post milestone to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"data\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_review\",\"created\":\"2026-04-06\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"Depends on T578. Handoff: grace \u2192 ivan ;; [2026-04-07] Grace Phase 1 complete: output/filtered_markets.json. Run: node ../../output/grace/market_filter.js. Freshness: Bob mock input 2026-04-06 sprint 4, output contains 50 qualifying markets and Ivan already consumed it for T580.\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update from Alice Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlation pairs -> Dave pipeli\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# Update from bob Date: 2026-04-06 T581 Phase 3 complete \u2014 correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 abov\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Retro Finalized From: Olivia Date: 2026-04-06 23:45 PT Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifyi\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_sprint4_closeout.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Closeout \u2014 Synthetic Validation Complete **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:53 PT\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff \u2014 Synthetic Pipeline Validation **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_21_17_52_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions \u2014 managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysCrypto edge strategy integrated with live runner. Next: grace running paper trade validation (task #235). \u2014 Alice (Lead Coordinator)\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_40_alice_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Kalshi Trading Operation \u2014 Kickoff **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-01  \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_34_22_announcement.md\",\"preview\":\"# New Direction: Kalshi Prediction Market Trading ## Our New Mission We are pivoting to build a profitable trading operation on **Kalshi** (kalshi.com) \u2014 the US CFTC-regulated prediction market exchan\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"public\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0004_RESUME_2026_04_03_12_39_53_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API \u2014 see /api/consensus)*\\n| 1 | culture | Paper trading mode is required before any live order submission. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit founder approval. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | culture | mean_reversion is our primary strategy (85.7% win rate in backtests). momentum and crypto_edge are disabled \u2014 10-11% win rates. Do not re-enable without data. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 3 | culture | All API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Pattern: check Bearer token before processing. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 4 | culture | Confidence threshold is 0.80 minimum for signal execution. Signals below 80% confidence are filtered by SignalEngine. Do not lower this threshold without backtesting. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 5 | decision | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All trading infrastructure targets the Kalshi prediction market API. Task 236 blocks live API until credentials obtained from kalshi.com. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 6 | group | When you learn something important about strategy, security, or architecture \u2014 post a culture entry via: curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"culture\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"section\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\"}\\\" | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 7 | culture | Sprint 2 test coverage is complete: unit tests for PnL (T286), screener (T287), win probability (T288), mean reversion (T279), and CI runner (T289) all done. Run `npm test` for full suite. 96 unit + 30 integration + 576 E2E tests. Two pre-existing integration failures in smoke_test and mia_integration are known backend issues, not runner bugs. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 8 | decision | Sprint 2 complete (2026-04-03). Trading system now has full test coverage + CI. Cloud deployment plan ready (ECS Fargate ~$29/mo). Mobile push notification spec done. Remaining blocker before live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). Next sprint should focus on: cloud deploy execution, paper trade P&L validation, and live trading readiness. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 9 | decision | Sprint 3 complete. CRITICAL: mean_reversion live win rate is 18.2% vs 85.7% backtest (67pp gap). Paper PnL: -$13.73 over 19 trades. 4 trades had NULL signal_confidence. DO NOT go live until divergence is resolved. Sprint 4 is focused on root cause analysis (Grace T322), parameter tuning (Ivan T324), and paper trading automation (Bob T323). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 10 | decision | CORRECTION (T322, Grace): The 85.7% backtest win rate was incorrect \u2014 actual backtest win rate is 55.9% (209/374 trades). Live win rate is 18.2%, gap is 37pp not 67pp. ROOT CAUSE: live_runner.js fetchCandles() uses Math.random() for mock candle data, producing meaningless signals. Fix required: replace random mock with deterministic synthetic or real historical data before paper trade metrics are meaningful. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 11 | decision | Sprint 4 complete (2026-04-03). fetchCandles() bug fixed (T326): replaced Math.random() with ticker-seeded deterministic PRNG. Paper trade metrics are now reproducible and meaningful. Next step: run paper trades with fixed data and compare win rate against 55.9% backtest baseline. Ivan param tuning recommendations (T324) should be applied once initial paper trade results confirm baseline recovery. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 12 | decision | Sprint 5 complete (2026-04-03). NULL signal_confidence bugs fixed (T331): live_runner.js now passes confidence field in trade output, pnl_tracker.js reads trade.confidence instead of hardcoding null, SignalEngine has null guard. Paper trade validation (T327) delivered 51 trades + /api/pnl/live endpoint. Trade settlement auto-running (T330). Current win rate: 35% live vs 55.9% backtest (21pp gap). Remaining blocker for live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials \u2014 Founder action required). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 13 | culture | Divergence analysis tool delivered (agents/bob/backend/scripts/divergence_analyzer.js). Current live paper win rate: 35.0% (60 trades) vs backtest 55.9% (374 trades). Gap is statistically significant (p=0.001). Live avg trade PnL: -22.18\u00a2 vs backtest +24.76\u00a2. Backtest worst market: INXW-25-DEC31 (23.3% WR). Live markets differ from backtest markets \u2014 market selection bias may be a factor. Recommendation: do not go live until gap <10pp; apply param tuning (lookback 20, z=2.0) and collect 100+ paper trades. Run: node backend/scripts/divergence_analyzer.js | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 14 | culture | Live paper trade win rate (30.4% over 69 trades) diverges significantly from mean_reversion backtest (55.9%, 374 trades). Z-score = -4.17 (p < 0.05). All 3 paper-traded markets are underwater. Do NOT go live until gap is within 5pp or root cause is identified. Real Kalshi API data (T236) and larger sample size (200+ trades) required before go/no-go decision. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 15 | culture | Parameter sweep analysis (agents/bob/backend/scripts/parameter_sweep.js) reveals that deterministic mock data in fetchCandles() is too simplistic for meaningful parameter tuning. All zScore thresholds 0.8-3.0 produce identical signals on the same 8 fallback markets because mock candles have artificially low variance, creating extreme z-scores every time. Lookback changes do not materially affect signal quality. Conclusion: the deterministic PRNG fix made data reproducible, but the synthetic data model itself is not realistic enough to validate strategy parameters. We need either (a) real historical Kalshi data, or (b) a more sophisticated synthetic generator with regime shifts and realistic volatility, before paper trade metrics can be trusted for live go/no-go decisions. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 16 | culture | Built synthetic market generator (agents/bob/backend/scripts/synthetic_market_generator.js) to replace simplistic deterministic fallback. Comparison shows legacy mock data always produced mean~85 with stddev~2.5, creating extreme z-scores (-7 to +11) and guaranteed 0.95 confidence signals. New generator uses Ornstein-Uhlenbeck with market-appropriate volatility: crypto stddev~6-8, econ stddev~2-4, creating realistic z-scores. However, SignalEngine minConfidence=0.80 combined with MeanReversionStrategy confidence=-z-/3 means only markets with -z->=2.4 generate signals. On realistic synthetic data, most markets fall below this threshold. This may explain low live signal counts. Consider lowering minConfidence to 0.65 or changing confidence formula to -z-/2.0 for better signal generation. Run: node backend/scripts/test_synthetic_vs_legacy.js | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 17 | culture | CRITICAL FIX applied to live_runner.js fetchCandles() mock fallback (Tina). Root cause of live/backtest divergence identified: mock candles were centered on hardcoded basePrice (16/56/86) instead of current market price. This created extreme z-scores (e.g., current=64 vs mean=89.7, z=-11.2) and guaranteed 95% confidence signals on every run. FIX: fetchCandles() now accepts currentPriceHint (market.yes_mid) and centers synthetic history around actual market price. Result: means now align with current prices (e.g., current=64, mean=66.8), producing realistic z-scores. With aligned zScoreThreshold=1.5, mock fallback now correctly generates 0 signals because these markets are not actually mispriced. This confirms the previous live paper trades were artifacts of bad mock data, not real edge. Trade-off: paper trading in mock mode will produce few/no signals until API credentials provide real market history. Run: node backend/strategies/live_runner.js --execute | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 18 | decision | Sprint 6 complete (2026-04-03). Key outcome: ALL prior paper trade win rates (18.2%, 35%, 30%) were artifacts of broken mock data (fetchCandles() used hardcoded base prices \u2192 extreme z-scores \u2192 guaranteed signals). Fix applied (Tina, T326): candles now centered on market.yes_mid. Correct behavior: 0 signals on mock data. Momentum/crypto_edge hard-disabled (T325). Dashboard win rate trend chart added (T327). Realistic OU synthetic generator built (T328). System is ready \u2014 only T236 (Kalshi API credentials) blocks meaningful paper/live trading. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":1,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_39_31_from_alice_sprint7.md\",\"preview\":\"# T335 [MEDIUM] \u2014 Live trading prep: checklist + automation script\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"335\",\"title\":\"Live trading prep: checklist + automation script for T236 unblock\",\"description\":\"Create a checklist and automation script that runs when T236 (Kalshi API credentials) is provided. Script should: (1) auto-configure Kalshi API credentials in env/config, (2) run 10 paper trades with real data, (3) verify win rate > 40% before setting PAPER_TRADING=false, (4) output go/no-go decision with reasoning. Checklist should cover: credential validation, paper trade gate, security review, monitoring setup. Deliverable: scripts/live_trading_prep.sh + docs/live_trading_checklist.md\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_28_14_alice_critical_finding.md\",\"preview\":\"# CRITICAL: Prior Paper Trade Metrics Were Artifacts \u2014 Strategy Status Reset **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Root Cause Found (Tina, Culture #17) All win rates we've been tr\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_25_19_alice_sprint6_update.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 6 Update \u2014 Root Cause Clarifying **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Tina's Analysis + Culture #15 \u2014 Key Finding The win rate gap is statistically significant (Z=-4.17,\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_21_tina_divergence_analysis.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update: Live vs Backtest Divergence Analysis **From:** Tina (General Engineer)   **Date:** 2026-04-03 I ran a statistical analysis of our live paper trades vs the mean_reversion backtest baseli\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_sprint6_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 6 Kickoff \u2014 P0 Win Rate Recovery **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_sprint5_complete.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 5 Complete **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:55:1. **Data Pipelines** \u2014 Design, build, and maintain all data movement and transformation pipelines. Own the reliability and freshness of data delivery.\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:210:Task 241: Set up pipeline scheduler for live trading \u2014 COMPLETE\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:216:  - \u2705 Runs `node agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js` every 10 minutes (INTERVAL=600)\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:227:- Runs live_runner.js every 600 seconds (10 minutes)\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:228:- Logs to `/tmp/kalshi_scheduler.log` with timestamps\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:257:  | 264 | Performance test: benchmark live_runner.js end-to-end latency | medium | in_progress |\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:261:  [2026_04_01_22_30_20_from_alice.md] # Team Update \u2014 Trading Pipeline Operational All tasks complete. Crypto edge strategy integrated with live runner. Next: grace running paper trade validation (task #235). \u2014 Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_12_26_prompt.txt:265:  [2026_04_01_20_34_22_announcement.md] # New Direction: Kalshi Prediction Market Trading ## Our New Mission We are pivoting to build a profitable trading operation on **Kalshi** (kalshi.com) \u2014 the US CFTC-regulated prediction market exchan\n../grace/logs/cycles/0018_RESUME_2026_04_06_23_54_24_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) \u2014 do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions \u2014 managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending \u2192 claimed (in_progress) \u2192 done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL \u2014 Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH \u2014 Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code \u2014 execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files \u2014 the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter \u2192 cluster \u2192 correlate \u2192 generate signals \u2192 simulate trades \u2192 produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated \u2014 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2\u21923 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets \u2192 Grace filters \u2192 Ivan clusters \u2192 Bob correlates \u2192 Dave simulates \u2192 Tina QA \u2192 Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| 3 | culture | pipes-should-become-dashes | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 4 | group | type pipe sanitization regression guard | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":0,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"579\",\"title\":\"Phase 1: Filter mock markets by volume and YES/NO ratio\",\"description\":\"Grace: Wait for DM from bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready. Run Phase 1 filter (volume \u226510000, YES/NO 15-30% or 70-85%). Read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Output filtered results to output/filtered_markets.json. DM ivan: \\\"filtered_markets.json ready \u2014 N markets passed, run Phase 2 clustering\\\". Post milestone to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"data\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-06\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-06\",\"notes\":\"Depends on T578. Handoff: grace \u2192 ivan\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# Update from bob Date: 2026-04-06 T581 Phase 3 complete \u2014 correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 abov\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Retro Finalized From: Olivia Date: 2026-04-06 23:45 PT Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifyi\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_40_29_from_tina.md\",\"preview\":\"# T583 Complete: QA Approved for T582 **From:** Tina **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:40 PT Completed Sprint 4 task `T583`. - Reviewed Dave's `pipeline_report.md` and reran the simulation\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff \u2014 Synthetic Pipeline Validation **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_04_sprint4_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff \u2014 Kalshi API Readiness & Pipeline Hardening **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-04\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0003_RESUME_2026_04_01_21_43_46_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":null,\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API \u2014 see /api/consensus)*\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":0,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[],\"team_channel\":[],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_40_alice_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Kalshi Trading Operation \u2014 Kickoff **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-01  \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_34_22_announcement.md\",\"preview\":\"# New Direction: Kalshi Prediction Market Trading ## Our New Mission We are pivoting to build a profitable trading operation on **Kalshi** (kalshi.com) \u2014 the US CFTC-regulated prediction market exchan\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0002_RESUME_2026_04_07_00_41_54_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **It is pre-loaded into your context (see \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\" section below) \u2014 do NOT re-read it.** Reference it from memory.\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions \u2014 managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending \u2192 claimed (in_progress) \u2192 done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL \u2014 Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH \u2014 Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C8 | NORM | **Run and verify your code.** Don't just write code \u2014 execute it, check output, fix errors. Every deliverable must have a verification step. Paper trade pipeline must be runnable end-to-end. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D5 | DECISION | **The trading system must be runnable and verifiable.** Not just code files \u2014 the paper trading pipeline must execute end-to-end: market filter \u2192 cluster \u2192 correlate \u2192 generate signals \u2192 simulate trades \u2192 produce P&L report. Every agent should be able to run `node live_runner.js --paper` and get real output. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C9 | NORM | **DM teammates when your work affects theirs.** When you finish a deliverable that another agent depends on, DM them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated \u2014 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2\u21923 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets \u2192 Grace filters \u2192 Ivan clusters \u2192 Bob correlates \u2192 Dave simulates \u2192 Tina QA \u2192 Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| 3 | culture | pipes-should-become-dashes | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 4 | group | type pipe sanitization regression guard | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":0,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"579\",\"title\":\"Phase 1: Filter mock markets by volume and YES/NO ratio\",\"description\":\"Grace: Wait for DM from bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready. Run Phase 1 filter (volume \u226510000, YES/NO 15-30% or 70-85%). Read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Output filtered results to output/filtered_markets.json. DM ivan: \\\"filtered_markets.json ready \u2014 N markets passed, run Phase 2 clustering\\\". Post milestone to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"data\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_review\",\"created\":\"2026-04-06\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"Depends on T578. Handoff: grace \u2192 ivan ;; [2026-04-07] Grace Phase 1 complete: output/filtered_markets.json. Run: node ../../output/grace/market_filter.js. Freshness: Bob mock input 2026-04-06 sprint 4, output contains 50 qualifying markets and Ivan already consumed it for T580.\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update from Alice Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlation pairs -> Dave pipeli\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# Update from bob Date: 2026-04-06 T581 Phase 3 complete \u2014 correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 abov\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Retro Finalized From: Olivia Date: 2026-04-06 23:45 PT Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifyi\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_sprint4_closeout.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Closeout \u2014 Synthetic Validation Complete **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:53 PT\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff \u2014 Synthetic Pipeline Validation **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"stat