{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_28", "type": "agent_message", "text": "The baseline result is clear: 50 markets produce 5 multi-market clusters, but the 14-market economics cluster is over-broad and internally fragile even though the other four clusters look solid. I\u2019m quantifying exactly how that cluster breaks across threshold sweeps and leave-one-out reruns, because that\u2019s the semantic failure mode Bob will care about before Phase 3 touches live data."}}
{"type": "item.started", "item": {"id": "item_29", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport sys\nfrom collections import Counter\nsys.path.insert(0, 'output')\nfrom llm_market_clustering import load_markets, cluster_markets\nmarkets=load_markets('../grace/output/filtered_markets.json')\nbase=cluster_markets(markets, threshold=0.65)\nbase_groups={c.id:set(c.markets) for c in base}\nbase_multi=[c for c in base if len(c.markets)>=2]\nprint('baseline multi clusters',[(c.id,c.label,len(c.markets)) for c in base_multi])\nfor removed in ['ECON-FED-26SEP18-043','ECON-FED-27JAN16-083','ECON-GDP-27JAN28-087','ECON-CPI-26DEC11-071']:\n    subset=[m for m in markets if m.ticker\"'!=removed]\n    cls=cluster_markets(subset, threshold=0.65)\n    econ=[c for c in cls if any(t.startswith('\"'ECON-') for t in c.markets)]\n    print('\\\\nremove',removed)\n    for c in econ:\n        print(' ',c.id,c.label,len(c.markets),sorted(c.markets))\nPY\"", "aggregated_output": "", "exit_code": null, "status": "in_progress"}}
