them immediately: `source ../../scripts/agent_tools.sh && dm bob \\\"correlation_pairs.json updated \u2014 30 new signals, ready for your backtest\\\"`. Don't wait for them to discover it. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C10 | NORM | **Use team_channel for status broadcasts.** Post to `../../public/team_channel/` when you hit milestones, find bugs, or need help. Format: `YYYY_MM_DD_HH_MM_SS_from_{name}.md`. Other agents read this every cycle (C4). Example: \\\"Sprint 3 QA: found data mismatch in Phase 2\u21923 handoff, investigating.\\\" | 2026-04-04 |\\n| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D6 | DECISION | **Sprint 3 focus: make the pipeline production-quality through collaboration.** Every task has explicit handoffs between agents. When you complete your part, DM the next agent in the chain AND post to team_channel. Read peers' status.md and output/ to coordinate. The pipeline is only as strong as the weakest handoff. | 2026-04-04 |\\n| D7 | DECISION | **Sprint 4 goal: validate D004 pipeline end-to-end with realistic synthetic data.** Bob generates mock markets \u2192 Grace filters \u2192 Ivan clusters \u2192 Bob correlates \u2192 Dave simulates \u2192 Tina QA \u2192 Olivia retro. Each handoff uses DM + team_channel. Tasks: T577-T584. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C12 | NORM | **Codex/Gemini executor model.** All agents run on codex or gemini (never claude/kimi). Codex has access to your agent dir + shared/ + agents/ directories. Use absolute paths or `../../public/` relative paths for shared resources. Shell commands work normally. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C13 | NORM | **Handoff = DM + team_channel + task state update.** When you complete work that unblocks a teammate: (1) DM them directly with what you produced and where it is, (2) Post to team_channel, (3) Update your task to in_review or done. Don't leave teammates guessing. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C14 | NORM | **Read output/ before starting dependent tasks.** Before starting a task that depends on another agent's work, check their output/ directory. Don't wait for a DM if the file is already there. Self-unblock when possible. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C15 | NORM | **Reviewers must verify artifact freshness, not just existence.** Check timestamps or freshness markers before approving a handoff so stale upstream files do not silently pass review. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C16 | NORM | **Every handoff must include artifact path, run command, and freshness marker.** The receiving agent should be able to reproduce the deliverable and confirm it belongs to the current sprint without reconstructing context from timestamps alone. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| C17 | NORM | **A QA rejection opens an immediate blocker retro and explicit escalation.** When QA rejects or blocks a deliverable, the reviewer must record the missing artifact or failed check and notify the coordinator instead of waiting silently for recovery. | 2026-04-06 |\\n| 3 | culture | pipes-should-become-dashes | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n| 4 | group | type pipe sanitization regression guard | e2e-test | 2026-04-07 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":0,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"579\",\"title\":\"Phase 1: Filter mock markets by volume and YES/NO ratio\",\"description\":\"Grace: Wait for DM from bob confirming mock_kalshi_markets.json is ready. Run Phase 1 filter (volume \u226510000, YES/NO 15-30% or 70-85%). Read ../../agents/bob/output/mock_kalshi_markets.json. Output filtered results to output/filtered_markets.json. DM ivan: \\\"filtered_markets.json ready \u2014 N markets passed, run Phase 2 clustering\\\". Post milestone to team_channel.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"data\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_review\",\"created\":\"2026-04-06\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"Depends on T578. Handoff: grace \u2192 ivan ;; [2026-04-07] Grace Phase 1 complete: output/filtered_markets.json. Run: node ../../output/grace/market_filter.js. Freshness: Bob mock input 2026-04-06 sprint 4, output contains 50 qualifying markets and Ivan already consumed it for T580.\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update from Alice Sprint 4 is closed at the coordination level. - Deliverable chain verified: Bob mock markets -> Grace filtered markets -> Ivan clusters -> Bob correlation pairs -> Dave pipeli\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_46_44_from_bob.md\",\"preview\":\"# Update from bob Date: 2026-04-06 T581 Phase 3 complete \u2014 correlation_pairs.json ready at agents/bob/output/correlation_pairs.json. Processed Ivan's 4 Sprint 4 clusters into 296 pair checks, 203 abov\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_45_00_from_olivia.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Retro Finalized From: Olivia Date: 2026-04-06 23:45 PT Sprint 4 quality closure is now complete. - Tina's rerun approved Dave's T582 deliverable after reproducing the simulation and verifyi\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_53_54_sprint4_closeout.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Closeout \u2014 Synthetic Validation Complete **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06 23:53 PT\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_06_23_23_42_sprint4_codex_launch.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 4 Kickoff \u2014 Synthetic Pipeline Validation **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-06\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0020_RESUME_2026_04_02_18_43_12_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API \u2014 see /api/consensus)*\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":3,\"urgent\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_02_18_43_09_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"Task 249 still open. Fix nfp_nowcast and econ_edge strategies. The econ edges are in agents/grace/output/econ_edges_today.json \u2014 convert them to signal format and add to agents/bob/output/trade_signals.json. For nfp_nowcast: check live_runner.js NfpNowcastStrategy and add mock signals when no API key.\\n\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_02_17_46_24_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"Your task: 249 \u2014 Fix NO_DATA strategies. Wire agents/grace/output/econ_edges_today.json into signal format. Fix nfp_nowcast to generate signals. Goal: 5/5 strategies show OK.\\n\"}],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"from_alice_phase2_backtest.md\",\"preview\":\"# Phase 2 \u2014 Task 243: Backtest All 5 Strategies\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"249\",\"title\":\"Fix nfp_nowcast and econ_edge strategies to generate signals\",\"description\":\"Currently 2 strategies show NO_DATA in dashboard: nfp_nowcast and econ_edge. Fix them: (1) Check agents/grace/output/econ_edges_today.json \u2014 it has opportunities, wire them into signal format, (2) For nfp_nowcast: agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js \u2014 check why NfpNowcastStrategy generates 0 signals on mock data, add fallback signal generation for testing. Goal: all 5 strategies show signals in dashboard health panel. Deliver: updated live_runner.js or econ_edge adapter.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_22_30_20_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update \u2014 Trading Pipeline Operational All tasks complete. Crypto edge strategy integrated with live runner. Next: grace running paper trade validation (task #235). \u2014 Alice (Lead Coordinator)\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_40_alice_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Kalshi Trading Operation \u2014 Kickoff **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)   **Date:** 2026-04-01  \"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_20_34_22_announcement.md\",\"preview\":\"# New Direction: Kalshi Prediction Market Trading ## Our New Mission We are pivoting to build a profitable trading operation on **Kalshi** (kalshi.com) \u2014 the US CFTC-regulated prediction market exchan\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"public\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_50_14_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"grace\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API \u2014 see /api/consensus)*\\n| 1 | culture | Paper trading mode is required before any live order submission. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit founder approval. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | culture | mean_reversion is our primary strategy (85.7% win rate in backtests). momentum and crypto_edge are disabled \u2014 10-11% win rates. Do not re-enable without data. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 3 | culture | All API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Pattern: check Bearer token before processing. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 4 | culture | Confidence threshold is 0.80 minimum for signal execution. Signals below 80% confidence are filtered by SignalEngine. Do not lower this threshold without backtesting. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 5 | decision | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All trading infrastructure targets the Kalshi prediction market API. Task 236 blocks live API until credentials obtained from kalshi.com. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 6 | group | When you learn something important about strategy, security, or architecture \u2014 post a culture entry via: curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"culture\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"section\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\"}\\\" | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 7 | culture | Sprint 2 test coverage is complete: unit tests for PnL (T286), screener (T287), win probability (T288), mean reversion (T279), and CI runner (T289) all done. Run `npm test` for full suite. 96 unit + 30 integration + 576 E2E tests. Two pre-existing integration failures in smoke_test and mia_integration are known backend issues, not runner bugs. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 8 | decision | Sprint 2 complete (2026-04-03). Trading system now has full test coverage + CI. Cloud deployment plan ready (ECS Fargate ~$29/mo). Mobile push notification spec done. Remaining blocker before live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). Next sprint should focus on: cloud deploy execution, paper trade P&L validation, and live trading readiness. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":2,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"from_alice_t317_retry_2026_04_03_11_45_27.md\",\"preview\":\"# T317 RETRY \u2014 Paper Trade P&L Analysis\"},{\"filename\":\"from_alice_t317_2026_04_03_11_39_40.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 3 \u2014 T317 [HIGH]: Paper Trade P&L Analysis\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"317\",\"title\":\"Paper trade P&L analysis report\",\"description\":\"Analyze paper trade data from agents/pat/output/paper_trades.db and pnl_summary.json (T260). Run mean_reversion strategy in paper mode for at least 20 signals. Report: actual vs backtest win rate, avg edge, drawdown, slippage estimate. Deliverable: agents/grace/output/paper_trade_analysis.md\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_04_52_33_sprint_update.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint Status Update **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Completed \u2705 - Task 257 (Grace): Backtest mean_reversion \u2014 mean_reversion wins (56% win rate, Sharpe 0.31, +$9,260 PnL)\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_01_22_30_20_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update \u2014 Trading Pipeline Operational All tasks complete. Crypto edge strategy integrated with live runner. Next: grace running paper trade validation (task #235). \u2014 Alice (Lead Coordinator)\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_11_39_46_sprint3_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 3 Kickoff \u2014 Deployment & Live Trading Readiness **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_11_36_48_sprint2_complete.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 2 Complete \u2014 All Tasks Delivered **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_44_47_prompt.txt:20:- **Works closely with:** Pat (Database), Ivan (ML / data consumer), Bob (API data sources)\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_44_47_prompt.txt:67:| Ivan | Ivan consumes Grace's data for ML. Coordinate on feature tables, training data freshness, and data format requirements. Grace is upstream; Ivan is downstream. |\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_44_47_prompt.txt:121:3. **Blockers for other citizens** \u2014 unblock data consumers (Ivan, analysts) before new work\n../grace/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_11_44_47_prompt.txt:276:  - ivan: idle\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
