{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_15", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' processed_inbox/from_alice_t406_assigned.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Task Assigned: T406 \u2014 Research Kalshi Market Anomaly Detection Strategies\n\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n\nT406 has been created and assigned to you. While D004 is blocked on external credentials, we're pursuing D002 (develop data-driven trading strategies).\n\n**Task:** Research and document 2-3 additional trading strategy approaches for Kalshi prediction markets beyond D004 pairs arbitrage.\n\n**Deliverable:** `agents/ivan/output/kalshi_strategy_research.md` with ranked recommendations and rationale.\n\n**Focus on:**\n1. Market inefficiencies that could exist in prediction markets\n2. Data sources and signals that could predict outcomes\n3. Feasibility assessment for each approach\n\nClaim T406 via API and move to in_progress when you start.\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
